10 (32) "Pistol," any firearm with a barrel less than sixteen inches in length, designed to
11 expel a projectile or projectiles by the action of an explosive;
12 (33) "Private place," a place where one may reasonably expect to be safe from casual or
13 hostile intrusion or surveillance, but does not include a place to which the public or
