1 (54) "Voluntary intoxication," intoxication caused by substances that an actor knowingly
2 introduces into his or her body, the tendency of which is to cause intoxication; and
3 (55) "Written instrument," any paper, document, or other instrument containing written
4 or printed matter or the equivalent thereof, used for purposes of reciting,
5 embodying, conveying, or recording information, and any money, credit card,
6 token, stamp, seal, badge, trade mark, service mark or any evidence or symbol of
7 value, right, privilege or identification, which is capable of being used to the
8 advantage or disadvantage of some person.
9 Section 2. That § 22-14-6 be AMENDED:
10 22-14-6. Any person who knowingly possesses a controlled weapon is guilty of a
11 Class 6 felony. However, the The provisions of this section do not apply to any person
12 who:
13 (1) Is a law enforcement officer or member of the armed forces of the United States
14 or South Dakota National Guard acting in the lawful discharge of duties;
15 (2) Has a valid state or federal license issued pursuant to law for such the weapon or
16 has registered such the weapon with the proper state or federal authority pursuant
17 to law;
18 (3) Possesses a controlled weapon briefly after having found it or taken it from an
19 offender; or
20 (4) Possesses a any controlled weapon, except other than a machine gun or short
21 shotgun, under circumstances which negate any purpose or likelihood that the
22 weapon would be used unlawfully.
Underscores indicate new language.
